{"questionId":"12206","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\gamma ^2} = \\gamma&nbsp; - 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>γ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>as&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\gamma \">\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n</math></span> is a root of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{z^2} - z + 1 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>z</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> then&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\gamma ^2} - \\gamma&nbsp; + 1 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>γ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\therefore {\\gamma ^2} = \\gamma&nbsp; - 1\">\n  <mo>∴</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>γ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for the use of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{z^2} - z + 1 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>z</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> in any way.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>R1</strong></em> for a correct reasoned approach.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD&nbsp;2</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\gamma ^2} = \\frac{{ - 1 + {\\text{i}}\\sqrt 3 }}{2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>γ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\gamma&nbsp; - 1 = \\frac{{1 + {\\text{i}}\\sqrt 3 }}{2} - 1 = \\frac{{ - 1 + {\\text{i}}\\sqrt 3 }}{2}\">\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>i</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12206","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.20a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that γ 2 = γ − 1 .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers introduction","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}